<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1435,1247,1487]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1356,1380]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
The identity of this species has been controversial in the literature. Together with 
<taxonomicName box="[1247,1435,1356,1380]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Pyralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centrana">
<emphasis box="[1247,1435,1356,1380]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pyralis centrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
F., 
<number box="[188,247,1391,1415]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1794.0">1794</number>
, it was long considered a doubtful synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Donovan, 1806" authorityName="Donovan" authorityYear="1806" box="[798,1171,1391,1416]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Acleris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notana">
<emphasis box="[798,965,1392,1416]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Acleris notana</emphasis>
(Donovan, 
<number box="[1102,1162,1391,1415]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1806.0">1806</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Speidel" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Speidel, W. &amp; Aarvik, L. (2002) Synonyms of European Tortricidae and Noctuidae, with special reference to the publications of Hubner, Geyer and Frolich. Nota Lepidopterologica, 25, 17 - 22." type="journal article" year="2002">
Speidel and Aarvik (
<number box="[245,304,1428,1452]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
contributed convincing evidence that it is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[963,1108,1428,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Acleris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugana">
<emphasis box="[963,1108,1428,1452]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">A. ferrugana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName box="[1168,1278,1428,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Acleris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notana">
<emphasis box="[1168,1278,1428,1452]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">A. notana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and this was followed by Brown (
<number box="[384,446,1463,1487]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2005.0">2005</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
